history.text: Hello! Have you ever seen The Notebook?

Yes, I have. It was a great movie and I would highly recommend it to anyone who enjoys romantic films. Are you familiar with any of the actors? Ryan Gosling, Rachel McAdams, Joan Allen, or James Marsden?
It's not really my chosen genre for film - to be honest, I read the book, and like stories that don't leave me crying. I did enjoy Rachel McAdams in Dr. Strange.

I've never read the book. I know it's by Nicholas Sparks, who happens to be one of my favorite authors. Although you don't like stories that leave you crying, I would still suggest watching it. It really is a great film all the way around in my opinion. I also really like the fact that it's narrated by someone else who is re-telling the story to a nursing home resident. That really sparked my interest.
A frame story, so to speak. It gives a good perspective to the plot.
